node.text: @msrachelhollis👇 (link in bio) We talk about loving yourself and seeing failure as success. We all need to learn to see the positive aspects of every failure in our life, to take proper care of ourselves by taking good care of our health, to sit down and process pain and grief at our own pace, and to never lose ourselves just to keep a relationship.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Jay Shetty on September 14, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'When you ask from a place of love and gratitude, the universe provides. Wher you ask from a place of anger and pain, negativity multiplies. GENIUS JAY SHETTY'.

node.text:
The *way* you receive determines *what* you receive. Comment a 💛 below if you needed this @jayshettygenius post today. ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Maintaining a state of gratitude and love only leads to greater abundance in your life 💫⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Deliberate love creates deeper love.⁠⁠
Consistent light creates brighter light.⁠⁠
Intentional hope creates stronger hope.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
This is what @jayshettygenius is all about. Weekly workshops, guided meditations, and a community centered in holistic well-being 🙏 ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Become a member today and I'll see you in the next workshop. Link in bio to join now! 👉 jayshettygenius.com

node.text: Drop a ❤️ below if you felt this👇Your pain is the beginning of discovering your potential, your passion and your purpose. When you use what hurt and broke you to help people heal their suffering, that’s what it is there for. I’ve seen people who have been through the most difficult situations transform the lives of others through their story and journey. Share it, love it, give it! It’s all about service

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Jay Shetty on September 12, 2021 tagging @charliemcdowell, and @lilyjcollins. May be an image of 3 people and people standing.

node.text: On September 4th 2021, I received one of the most precious honors, to officiate the wedding of my dear friends @lilyjcollins & @charliemcdowell | Words cannot explain how beautiful these two humans are. They have the biggest and kindest hearts and bring so much joy to so many. Lily & Charlie asked for the most unique ceremony. This moment captured here was during the meditation before the vows. They wanted to start with deep presence, alignment with nature and grounding in the moment. This is just a little glimpse into these magical souls. I am so humbled and grateful to be part of your journey. Congratulations Lily & Charlie, we are here for you both forever and feel so blessed to experience your love. Please send them both ALL your love, positive energy and wishes for this next step in their journey. PS A BIG thank you to both your families for making us feel like family. We haven’t seen ours in a long time but felt so much love!
